						<summary>

						<p>This is much damaged. It belongs to the Vijayanagar king <hi rend="bold">Viruppaṇa-Uḍaiyar (Virūpāksha I)</hi> and is dated in the cyclic year Piṅgaḷa (which corresponds to Śaka 1299,) Āṉi 14. It seems to record an instrument of assurance addressed to the <hi rend="italic">Tandirimār</hi> of Kalvāśal-nāḍu, Kāṉanāḍu and other places declaring Malaiyālaṅguḍi to be a place of refuge for all of them. It corresponds to the <hi rend="italic">Añjināṉpugaliḍam</hi> “the asylum for the fear-stricken” of other inscriptions.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
